benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve invoice item audit logs with history by id

covered: Valid Request: Scenario TC01 covers successful retrieval with valid invoice item ID.
Empty Response: Scenario TC02 covers case when no audit logs are present for an existing invoice item.
Invalid invoice item ID format: Scenario TC04 tests malformed UUID input.
Not Found: Scenario TC03 covers non-existent invoice item IDs resulting in 404.
Authorization: Scenarios TC05 and TC06 cover missing and invalid authentication tokens.
Error Handling: Scenario TC08 covers system unavailability (503).
Large Data Handling: Scenario TC09 tests large audit log payloads and performance.
Security: Scenarios TC10 and TC11 test for SQL injection and XSS attempts.
Regression: Scenario TC12 ensures previously fixed issues remain fixed.
Backward Compatibility: Scenario TC13 covers older client headers.
Concurrency: Scenario TC14 tests multiple simultaneous requests.
Response Time: Scenario TC15 addresses performance under load.
Content-Type Header: Scenario TC16 verifies correct response headers.
Partial Input: Scenario TC17 tests incomplete or truncated IDs.
Empty Database: Scenario TC18 covers case when no invoice items exist.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test for caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate or verify rate limiting or throttling.
Edge Cases: No tests for extremely large or malformed query parameters beyond ID format.
Response Content Validation: No detailed validation of the structure and fields within the AuditLog objects beyond presence.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to verify correct handling of large result sets.
Include scenarios that verify caching headers and cache validation mechanisms.
Implement rate limiting tests to ensure system handles high request volumes gracefully.
Create additional edge case tests for malformed or unsupported query parameters.
Enhance validation of response body to check for completeness and correctness of AuditLog object fields.
